OL,4,C'feared for her life' after collapsing
OL,6,FBy the time her father and George made
OL,7,Fit into town, Simone had started
OL,8,Fhaving seizures.
OL,10,FGeorge said: "I don't scare easily and
OL,11,FI was scared. At one point I thought
OL,12,Fshe might die, because of the way she
OL,13,Fwas reacting.
OL,15,F"She would go absolutely rigid almost
OL,16,Fas though it was a seizure or a stroke
OL,17,Fand I'm thinking 'oh my God, what if
OL,18,Fshe has a brain aneurysm or something."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/12
