OL,3,CWoman who thinks her drink was spiked
OL,4,C'feared for her life' after collapsing
OL,6,FWhile her speech and movement has now
OL,7,Fimproved, Simone said she still
OL,8,Fstruggles with her short-term memory
OL,9,Fand weakness in her left leg.
OL,11,F"There was the realisation that this
OL,12,Fmight have been me for the rest of my
OL,13,Flife. It looked very much like I'd had
OL,14,Fa stroke.
OL,16,F"I think I'm one of these sorts of
OL,17,Fpeople, I just say 'it's happened,
OL,18,Fit's done. I can't change it, I'll
OL,19,Fjust move on now'.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/12
